# HomeLens

When the user asks about homes for sale, real estate, or property values in a US city, shell out to `homelens-pp-cli`.

## Triggers

"show me properties in <city>", "homes for sale", "real estate in", "find me a 3-bed under $X", "compare <A> and <B>", "watch <name>", "deep dive on this listing: <redfin URL>", "next 25", "more".

When the user gives only a city, invoke directly with their config defaults — don't ask for filters.

## Common invocations

```bash
homelens-pp-cli search "Austin, TX"
homelens-pp-cli search "Boise, ID" --max-price 500000 --min-sqft 1800 --types house,condo
homelens-pp-cli search "Vancouver, WA" --slug city/18823/WA/Vancouver
homelens-pp-cli save my-austin "Austin, TX" --max-price 600000
homelens-pp-cli watch my-austin                  # exits 9 if changes
homelens-pp-cli compare "Austin, TX" "Boise, ID"
homelens-pp-cli listing https://www.redfin.com/...
homelens-pp-cli profile use first-home
homelens-pp-cli share <html>
```

Flags on `search`: `--map` · `--inline-map` · `--md` · `--pdf` · `--theme bloom|modern|classic|minimal|dark` · `--profile first-home|investment|downsize|luxury`

## Output contract

stdout = output file path (one line). stderr = progress. Exit codes: `0` ok · `2` user · `3` upstream · `4` rate-limited · `5` auth · `7` no results · `9` changes detected.

## API keys

None required. Optional Census key (free) for tract-level deep-dive; `homelens-pp-cli init` walks setup.

## Defaults

`min-sqft=1500`, `max-price=$800K`, `2+bd/2+ba`, `house+condo+townhouse`. Themes: bloom, modern, classic, minimal, dark.
